This paper deals with the analysis of cryptographic protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of Horn theories, which is related to logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The reduction technique proposed in the paper involves solving the derivation problem, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of tools such as ProVerif, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
